SIMPLE: institutor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Institutor
<hw>In"sti*tu`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>instituteur</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who institutes, founds, ordains, or
establishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who educates; an instructor.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Walker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Episcopal Church)</fld> <def>A presbyter appointed
by the bishop to institute a rector or assistant minister over a parish
church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instop</ent>⟦br⟧
